messages.messageBody:
-=-i have seen the image of the kokopelli before but never paid
attention to what she's all about! -=-

He. Definitely a he. Take it all with a grain of salt, though. For
people to expand on what they find carved on rocks is interesting but
speculative. Something that might help with that is a book called
"Motel of the Mysteries," an illustrated book (short, funny) about
future archeologists discovering a buried hotel from the 1970's and
explaining all the items they find, including the shrine, with the
"scientists" modelling the ways in which those people worshipped.

Sandra
